<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The following code shows three attempts to create a Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_DateTextBox using a dojox.widget Calendar as popupClass.</p>

<p>The MonthAndYearly Calendar works fine!</p>

<p>The YearlyCalendar is displayed correctly too. But after selecting a value nothing happens with the DateTextBox - it stays empty.</p>

<p>I've added a markup version as third attempt to demonstrate that the Widget by Dojo itself seems to work fine.</p>

<p>Can't tell if it is a major Dojo problem with the popupClass in a DateTextBox or if it is caused by the Zend_Form_Element.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?= new Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_DateTextBox(
    'monthAndYearly',
    array(
        'dijitParams' =&gt; array(
            'popupClass' =&gt; 'dojox.widget.MonthAndYearlyCalendar'
        )
    )
);
?&gt;
&lt;?= new Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_DateTextBox(
    'yearly',
    array(
        'dijitParams' =&gt; array(
            'popupClass' =&gt; 'dojox.widget.YearlyCalendar',
            #'popupClass' =&gt; 'dojox.widget.MonthAndYearlyCalendar'
        )
    )
);
?&gt;
